     Calculating new penalty parameter lambda.

_U_s_a_g_e:

     new.lambda(penden.env,lambda0)

_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

penden.env: Containing all information, environment of pendensity()

 lambda0: actual penalty parameter lambda

_D_e_t_a_i_l_s:

     Iterating for the lambda is stopped, when the changes between the
     old and the new lambda is smaller than 0.01*lambda0. If this
     criterion isn't reached, the iteration is terminated after 11
     iterations.

     The iteration formulae is

              lambda=(beta^T D_m beta)/(df(lambda)-(m-1)

